Use skip for any reason.
@unittest.skip('just because')

Use skipIf to check a library version.
@unittest.skipIf(int(sys.version[0]) >4, 'needs to be version 4')

Use skipUnless to check the OS.
Ex. @unittest.skipUnless(sys.platform.startswith('win'), 'Windows OS required')

Use expectedFailure if the tests are going to pass for sure.
@unittest.expectedFailure